Package: hsa-snoop
Version: PLACEHOLDER
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Stephen Bates <sbates@raithlin.com>
Depends: systemd, bpftrace
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Description: HSA/HIP AQL queue snooper with Prometheus metrics exporter
 hsa-snoop monitors AMD GPU HSA/HIP AQL command queues, SDMA DMA copy engines,
 and AMD Infinity Storage (AIS) P2P direct-IO operations at the kernel level
 using kprobes and bpftrace. When installed via this package it runs as a
 systemd service in Prometheus mode (--all --prometheus --ais-snoop), exposing
 live GPU queue metrics at http://localhost:9488/metrics.
 .
 AIS snooping captures per-GPU and per-PCIe-device read/write throughput,
 IOPS, latency histograms, IO size distributions, and error events for AMD
 Infinity Storage direct-storage transfers (requires amdgpu DKMS >= 6.19 with
 CONFIG_PCI_P2PDMA and a large-BAR dGPU).
